descriptionByLocale.en:
**Senior Backend Developer**

**Job Description**

ELP SA is a financial services company based in Chiasso, part of the ELP group. The candidate will be integrated into the cambiavalute.ch project and report directly to the product manager.

**Responsibilities:**

- Design, develop, and maintain RESTful APIs in C#;
- Manage and optimize SQL databases (MS SQL);
- Collaborate with the team to ensure a smooth integration between systems;
- Implement scalability, security, and performance strategies for backend applications;
- Write clean, documented, and tested code.

**Requirements:**

- 5+ years of experience in backend development;
- Excellent knowledge of C# and MS SQL;
- Experience with backend frameworks;
- Familiarity with cloud environments (preferably Azure);
- Ability to work in a team and communicate effectively, including in English;
- Knowledge of the financial sector. Previous experience in online trading, banking, or cryptocurrencies is a preferred title.

**Plus:**

- Experience with microservices and serverless architectures;
- Knowledge of monitoring and logging tools;
- Knowledge of testing tools;
- Experience with CI/CD and automation of development processes;
- Familiarity with FaaS and PaaS services.

**Work Type:**

- Full-time, indefinite contract.

**How to Apply:**

- Send your CV in PDF format to hr@elp-group.com.

**Note:** Only applications that meet all the requirements listed above will be considered.

**Why Choose Us?**

Cambiavalute.ch is the Swiss specialist in online currency exchange. Exchange comfortably from home and save up to 80% compared to bank and currency exchange office rates.

